From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Tetsuya Hayashi <tetsu.h@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] installer: map Debian 12 (bookworm) to Ubuntu jammy for the
 Tenstorrent PPA

The Tenstorrent apt repository at ``https://ppa.tenstorrent.com/debian/``
currently publishes only a ``trixie`` pocket (Debian 13). On Debian 12
("bookworm") the upstream installer derives the pocket name from
``VERSION_CODENAME=bookworm`` and the resulting ``apt-get update`` aborts
with HTTP 404, which prevents the rest of the installer from running.

Until Tenstorrent ships a bookworm pocket, fall back to the Ubuntu
``jammy`` pocket (22.04 LTS) when the running release is bookworm. This
is safe because:

  * glibc compatibility: jammy packages are built against glibc 2.35,
    which is forward-compatible with bookworm's glibc 2.36.
  * Package availability: the Ubuntu jammy pocket provides the full
    package set (tt-metalium, tt-nn, tt-smi, etc.), whereas the Debian
    trixie pocket only provides a limited subset (pyluwen, sfpi, dkms).

Tested on:
  * Debian 12 (bookworm)  -> bookworm remapped to jammy (Ubuntu PPA)
  * Debian 13 (trixie)    -> uses VERSION_CODENAME=trixie unchanged (Debian PPA)

Upstream-Status: Pending [tenstorrent/tt-installer]
Signed-off-by: Tetsuya Hayashi <tetsu.h@gmail.com>
---
 install.m4 | 19 +++++++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/install.m4 b/install.m4
index 0000000..0000001 100644
--- a/install.m4
+++ b/install.m4
@@ -749,8 +749,23 @@ install_tt_repos () {
 		"debian")
 			# Add the apt listing
 			# shellcheck disable=2002
-			echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/tt-pkg-key.asc] https://ppa.tenstorrent.com/debian/ $( cat /etc/os-release | grep "^VERSION_CODENAME=" | sed 's/^VERSION_CODENAME=//' ) main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/tenstorrent.list > /dev/null
-
+			# Extract the codename from /etc/os-release.
+			codename=$(cat /etc/os-release | grep "^VERSION_CODENAME=" | sed 's/^VERSION_CODENAME=//')
+			# ppa.tenstorrent.com/debian only publishes a trixie pocket;
+			# map Debian 12 (bookworm) to the Ubuntu jammy pocket, which has
+			# compatible glibc (2.35 vs bookworm's 2.36) and provides the
+			# full package set (tt-metalium, tt-nn, etc.).
+			case "${codename}" in
+				bookworm)
+					ppa_url="https://ppa.tenstorrent.com/ubuntu/"
+					codename="jammy"
+					;;
+				*)
+					ppa_url="https://ppa.tenstorrent.com/debian/"
+					;;
+			esac
+			echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/tt-pkg-key.asc] ${ppa_url} ${codename} main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/tenstorrent.list > /dev/null
+
 			# Setup the keyring
 			sudo mkdir -p /etc/apt/keyrings; sudo chmod 755 /etc/apt/keyrings
 
